Popular gospel artist, Chinedu Nwadike, has passed on. Chinedu Nwadike died on Sunday at the age of 39 years after long years of contending with cancer.
Chinedu Nwadike suffered chronic kidney infection for few weeks before his death. Though, family sources said he had recovered and was planning to travel to India for treatment of blood cancer this week, but suddenly died on Sunday.
Chinedu left behind his wife, Dorah Chinedu Nwadike, and three children. Chinedu Nwadike was  Special Assistant on Mobilization to Governor Hope Uzodinma of Imo State till his death on Sunday.
Chinedu started as a dancer with Gozie Okeke gospel music band.
